        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>PROCEDURES FOR MEASURING EXHAUST SMOKE VARY FROM STATE TO STATE. THESE DIFFERENCES MAKE IT
                    IMPRACTICAL TO PROVIDE A UNIVERSALLY USEFUL METHOD OF MEASURING EXHAUST SMOKE. WHEN REQUIRED,
                    CONSULT YOUR STATE REGULATORY AGENCY FOR GUIDANCE.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <para>When confronted with an excessive exhaust smoke condition after completing all the diagnostic tests (and
            correcting any area not to specifications), check the following:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Glow Plug Continuity - (Refer to Test A of CGED-470-* and Section 6, page 5).</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If continuity is NOT OK, continue completion of CGED-470-*, "SOLID STATE GLOW PLUG
                    TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE".
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
